}
ORDER BY ?zone

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.4/Brick#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?zoneLabel ?propLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # Get the zone (label optional)\\n  ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?zone rdfs:label ?zoneLabel }\\n\\n  # Pattern 1: zone directly related to a Property\\n  { ?zone brick:hasPoint ?prop . }\\n  UNION\\n  # Pattern 2: zone -> two hops -> RoomDomainSpace -> contains -> Property\\n  { ?zone (brick:hasPart|brick:hasLocation){2} ?rds .\\n    ?rds a brick:RoomDomainSpace .\\n    ?rds brick:contains ?prop .\\n  }\\n\\n  # The entity we have is a Property (or subclass)\\n  ?prop a brick:Property .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?prop rdfs:label ?propLabel }\\n\\n  # External reference with writable = false\\n  ?prop brick:hasExternalReference ?ext .\\n  ?ext brick:writable false .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?ext brick:alcEndpoint ?alcEndpoint }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?ext brick:mpcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?zoneLabel ?propLabel"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-2129b5b0528f46db8995079c2f9109e0', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 46, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.3/Brick#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>\\nPREFIX ex: <http://example.org/>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?property ?propertyLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # Identify Zone instances (including those reachable via Room domain spaces and chained connections)\\n  {\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Zones reachable from a Room via any chain of object properties (up to a reasonable depth)\\n    ?room a brick:Room .\\n    ?room ( ?p1 / ?p2* ) ?zone .\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Find properties that have the zone as a domain (directly or via rdfs:domain chain)\\n  {\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Chained domain: properties whose domain is a class that is a subclass of Zone\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?domainClass .\\n    ?domainClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Property must be marked as read\\u2011only. Assuming a SHACL shape or custom annotation defines this.\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property ex:isReadOnly true }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property sh:readOnly true }\\n  FILTER ( bound(?property) && ( ?property ex:isReadOnly true || ?property sh:readOnly true ) )\\n\\n  # Retrieve the human\\u2011readable label for the property\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property rdfs:label ?propertyLabel }\\n  BIND (COALESCE(?propertyLabel, STR(?property)) AS ?propertyLabel)\\n\\n  # External references (assuming they are linked via a property ex:externalReference to a resource that provides alc and mpc endpoints)\\n  OPTIONAL {\\n    ?property ex:externalReference ?extRef .\\n    ?extRef ex:alcEndpoint ?alcEndpoint ;\\n            ex:mpcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint .\\n  }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?property"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-71ed5b0ea3e94146bbaeecd2bfd673e8', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 46, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.3/Brick#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>\\nPREFIX ex: <http://example.org/>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?property ?propertyLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # Identify Zone instances (including those reachable via Room domain spaces and chained connections)\\n  {\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Zones reachable from a Room via any chain of object properties (up to a reasonable depth)\\n    ?room a brick:Room .\\n    ?room ( ?p1 / ?p2* ) ?zone .\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Find properties that have the zone as a domain (directly or via rdfs:domain chain)\\n  {\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Chained domain: properties whose domain is a class that is a subclass of Zone\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?domainClass .\\n    ?domainClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Property must be marked as read\\u2011only. Assuming a SHACL shape or custom annotation defines this.\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property ex:isReadOnly true }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property sh:readOnly true }\\n  FILTER ( bound(?property) && ( ?property ex:isReadOnly true || ?property sh:readOnly true ) )\\n\\n  # Retrieve the human\\u2011readable label for the property\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property rdfs:label ?propertyLabel }\\n  BIND (COALESCE(?propertyLabel, STR(?property)) AS ?propertyLabel)\\n\\n  # External references (assuming they are linked via a property ex:externalReference to a resource that provides alc and mpc endpoints)\\n  OPTIONAL {\\n    ?property ex:externalReference ?extRef .\\n    ?extRef ex:alcEndpoint ?alcEndpoint ;\\n            ex:mpcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint .\\n  }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?property"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-71ed5b0ea3e94146bbaeecd2bfd673e8', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 46, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.3/Brick#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>\\nPREFIX ex: <http://example.org/>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?property ?propertyLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # Identify Zone instances (including those reachable via Room domain spaces and chained connections)\\n  {\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Zones reachable from a Room via any chain of object properties (up to a reasonable depth)\\n    ?room a brick:Room .\\n    ?room ( ?p1 / ?p2* ) ?zone .\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Find properties that have the zone as a domain (directly or via rdfs:domain chain)\\n  {\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Chained domain: properties whose domain is a class that is a subclass of Zone\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?domainClass .\\n    ?domainClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Property must be marked as read\\u2011only. Assuming a SHACL shape or custom annotation defines this.\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property ex:isReadOnly true }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property sh:readOnly true }\\n  FILTER ( bound(?property) && ( ?property ex:isReadOnly true || ?property sh:readOnly true ) )\\n\\n  # Retrieve the human\\u2011readable label for the property\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property rdfs:label ?propertyLabel }\\n  BIND (COALESCE(?propertyLabel, STR(?property)) AS ?propertyLabel)\\n\\n  # External references (assuming they are linked via a property ex:externalReference to a resource that provides alc and mpc endpoints)\\n  OPTIONAL {\\n    ?property ex:externalReference ?extRef .\\n    ?extRef ex:alcEndpoint ?alcEndpoint ;\\n            ex:mpcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint .\\n  }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?property"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-71ed5b0ea3e94146bbaeecd2bfd673e8', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 46, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

ModelResponse(parts=[TextPart(content='{\n  "sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/Brick#>\\nPREFIX std:   <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>\\nPREFIX rdfs:  <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\n\\nSELECT ?zone ?zoneLabel ?propLabel ?alcRef ?mpcRef WHERE {\\n  # -- every Zone (including subclasses)\\n  ?zone a std:Zone .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?zone rdfs:label ?zoneLabel . }\\n\\n  # -- non‑writable points/properties that are associated with the zone\\n  #    (the model may use either Brick\'s hasPoint or Standard223\'s hasProperty)\\n  ?zone (brick:hasPoint|std:hasProperty) ?prop .\\n  ?prop rdfs:label ?propLabel .\\n  ?prop brick:writable false .\\n\\n  # -- optional ALC endpoint reference (generic \\"endpoint\\" predicate in Brick)\\n  OPTIONAL { ?zone brick:endpoint ?alcRef . }\\n\\n  # -- optional MPC endpoint reference (MPC DB name predicate in Brick)\\n  OPTIONAL { ?zone brick:mpc_db_name ?mpcRef . }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?zone"\n}', part_kind='text')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 46, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.4/Brick#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?zoneLabel ?propLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # Get the zone (label optional)\\n  ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?zone rdfs:label ?zoneLabel }\\n\\n  # Pattern 1: zone directly related to a Property\\n  { ?zone brick:hasPoint ?prop . }\\n  UNION\\n  # Pattern 2: zone -> two hops -> RoomDomainSpace -> contains -> Property\\n  { ?zone (brick:hasPart|brick:hasLocation){2} ?rds .\\n    ?rds a brick:RoomDomainSpace .\\n    ?rds brick:contains ?prop .\\n  }\\n\\n  # The entity we have is a Property (or subclass)\\n  ?prop a brick:Property .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?prop rdfs:label ?propLabel }\\n\\n  # External reference with writable = false\\n  ?prop brick:hasExternalReference ?ext .\\n  ?ext brick:writable false .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?ext brick:alcEndpoint ?alcEndpoint }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?ext brick:mpcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?zoneLabel ?propLabel"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-2129b5b0528f46db8995079c2f9109e0', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 46, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.3/Brick#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>\\nPREFIX ex: <http://example.org/>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?property ?propertyLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # Identify Zone instances (including those reachable via Room domain spaces and chained connections)\\n  {\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Zones reachable from a Room via any chain of object properties (up to a reasonable depth)\\n    ?room a brick:Room .\\n    ?room ( ?p1 / ?p2* ) ?zone .\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Find properties that have the zone as a domain (directly or via rdfs:domain chain)\\n  {\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Chained domain: properties whose domain is a class that is a subclass of Zone\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?domainClass .\\n    ?domainClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Property must be marked as read\\u2011only. Assuming a SHACL shape or custom annotation defines this.\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property ex:isReadOnly true }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property sh:readOnly true }\\n  FILTER ( bound(?property) && ( ?property ex:isReadOnly true || ?property sh:readOnly true ) )\\n\\n  # Retrieve the human\\u2011readable label for the property\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property rdfs:label ?propertyLabel }\\n  BIND (COALESCE(?propertyLabel, STR(?property)) AS ?propertyLabel)\\n\\n  # External references (assuming they are linked via a property ex:externalReference to a resource that provides alc and mpc endpoints)\\n  OPTIONAL {\\n    ?property ex:externalReference ?extRef .\\n    ?extRef ex:alcEndpoint ?alcEndpoint ;\\n            ex:mpcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint .\\n  }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?property"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-71ed5b0ea3e94146bbaeecd2bfd673e8', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 46, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.3/Brick#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>\\nPREFIX ex: <http://example.org/>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?property ?propertyLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # Identify Zone instances (including those reachable via Room domain spaces and chained connections)\\n  {\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Zones reachable from a Room via any chain of object properties (up to a reasonable depth)\\n    ?room a brick:Room .\\n    ?room ( ?p1 / ?p2* ) ?zone .\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Find properties that have the zone as a domain (directly or via rdfs:domain chain)\\n  {\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Chained domain: properties whose domain is a class that is a subclass of Zone\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?domainClass .\\n    ?domainClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Property must be marked as read\\u2011only. Assuming a SHACL shape or custom annotation defines this.\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property ex:isReadOnly true }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property sh:readOnly true }\\n  FILTER ( bound(?property) && ( ?property ex:isReadOnly true || ?property sh:readOnly true ) )\\n\\n  # Retrieve the human\\u2011readable label for the property\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property rdfs:label ?propertyLabel }\\n  BIND (COALESCE(?propertyLabel, STR(?property)) AS ?propertyLabel)\\n\\n  # External references (assuming they are linked via a property ex:externalReference to a resource that provides alc and mpc endpoints)\\n  OPTIONAL {\\n    ?property ex:externalReference ?extRef .\\n    ?extRef ex:alcEndpoint ?alcEndpoint ;\\n            ex:mpcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint .\\n  }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?property"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-71ed5b0ea3e94146bbaeecd2bfd673e8', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 46, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')

PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/Brick/>
PREFIX b223: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?ahu ?ahuLabel ?propLabel ?alc ?mpc
WHERE {
  # Air Handling Units whose label includes "RTU"
  ?ahu a b223:AirHandlingUnit .
  ?ahu rdfs:label ?ahuLabel .
  FILTER(CONTAINS(LCASE(?ahuLabel), "rtu"))

  # Properties related to the AHU
  ?ahu b223:hasProperty ?prop .
  ?prop rdfs:label ?propLabel .

  # Keep only non‑writable properties
  FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?prop brick:writable true }

  # Optional ALC and MPC endpoint references
  OPTIONAL { ?prop brick:alc_db_name ?alc }
  OPTIONAL { ?prop brick:mpc_db_name ?mpc }
}
ORDER BY ?ahuLabel ?propLabel

ModelResponse(parts=[ToolCallPart(tool_name='final_result', args='{"sparql_query": "PREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/1.3/Brick#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>\\nPREFIX ex: <http://example.org/>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?property ?propertyLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # Identify Zone instances (including those reachable via Room domain spaces and chained connections)\\n  {\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Zones reachable from a Room via any chain of object properties (up to a reasonable depth)\\n    ?room a brick:Room .\\n    ?room ( ?p1 / ?p2* ) ?zone .\\n    ?zone a brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Find properties that have the zone as a domain (directly or via rdfs:domain chain)\\n  {\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?zone .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Chained domain: properties whose domain is a class that is a subclass of Zone\\n    ?property rdfs:domain ?domainClass .\\n    ?domainClass rdfs:subClassOf* brick:Zone .\\n  }\\n\\n  # Property must be marked as read\\u2011only. Assuming a SHACL shape or custom annotation defines this.\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property ex:isReadOnly true }\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property sh:readOnly true }\\n  FILTER ( bound(?property) && ( ?property ex:isReadOnly true || ?property sh:readOnly true ) )\\n\\n  # Retrieve the human\\u2011readable label for the property\\n  OPTIONAL { ?property rdfs:label ?propertyLabel }\\n  BIND (COALESCE(?propertyLabel, STR(?property)) AS ?propertyLabel)\\n\\n  # External references (assuming they are linked via a property ex:externalReference to a resource that provides alc and mpc endpoints)\\n  OPTIONAL {\\n    ?property ex:externalReference ?extRef .\\n    ?extRef ex:alcEndpoint ?alcEndpoint ;\\n            ex:mpcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint .\\n  }\\n}\\nORDER BY ?property"}', tool_call_id='chatcmpl-tool-71ed5b0ea3e94146bbaeecd2bfd673e8', part_kind='tool-call')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 21, 17, 46, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')
